PK — ab Decorator Pattern ko bhi “deep + interview + real system” clarity me lock kar dete hain 🔥
Tumne jo padha hai wo sahi hai — ab usko simplify + sharpen karte hain.

🧠 1️⃣ Core Definition (1 line)
Decorator Pattern allows you to add behavior to an object dynamically without changing its original class.
🧠 Aha
Inheritance nahi → wrapping use karte hain
🍕 2️⃣ Intuition (Pizza example — BEST)
Base
Margherita Pizza
Add features (stacking)
+ Cheese
+ Mushroom
+ Paneer
Final
Pizza = Base + Feature1 + Feature2 + Feature3
🧠 Aha
Layer by layer build hota hai object
🚨 3️⃣ Problem without Decorator
❌ Approach
MargheritaCheese
MargheritaPaneer
MargheritaCheeseMushroom
MargheritaPaneerVeggies
...
💥 Result
Class Explosion 🚨
🧠 Aha
Combination = infinite classes
✅ 4️⃣ Solution: Decorator Pattern
🧩 Structure
🟢 Base Interface
Pizza
🔵 Concrete Base
Margherita
Farmhouse
🟡 Decorator (abstract)
ToppingDecorator implements Pizza
🔴 Concrete Decorators
Cheese
Mushroom
Paneer
🧠 Aha
Decorator bhi Pizza hai
🔥 5️⃣ Most Important Concept
👉 This line samajh lo:
Decorator HAS-A Pizza
Decorator IS-A Pizza
🧠 Aha
Inheritance + Composition combo
⚙️ 6️⃣ Flow (step-by-step)
Step 1
Pizza p = new Farmhouse();
Step 2
p = new Cheese(p);
Step 3
p = new Mushroom(p);
Final
Farmhouse + Cheese + Mushroom
🧠 Aha
Har layer previous ko wrap kar raha hai
🔥 7️⃣ Call Flow (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)
Call:
p.getCost();
Flow:
Mushroom.getCost()
  → Cheese.getCost()
      → Farmhouse.getCost()
Calculation:
200 (base)
+ 20 (cheese)
+ 40 (mushroom)
= 260
🧠 Aha
Execution inside → outside hota hai
🎯 8️⃣ When to Use (INTERVIEW GOLD)

Use Decorator when:

1. Runtime pe behavior add karna ho
2. Multiple combinations ho
3. Feature stacking ho
4. Class explosion avoid karna ho
🧠 Shortcut
Layering dikhe → Decorator socho
⚔️ 9️⃣ Decorator vs Inheritance
❌ Inheritance
Rigid
Compile-time
Class explosion
✅ Decorator
Flexible
Runtime
Reusable
🧠 Aha
Inheritance = static
Decorator = dynamic
🔥 10️⃣ Real World Examples
☕ Coffee (classic)
Coffee + Milk + Sugar + Whip
🧾 Logging System
Base Logger
+ Timestamp
+ File logging
+ Encryption
🧠 Aha
Same object → different behaviors
🌐 Java Real Example
BufferedReader → wraps FileReader

👉 This is decorator 🔥

🚨 11️⃣ Common Mistakes
❌ 1. Overuse
Too many layers → debugging tough
❌ 2. Wrong abstraction
Decorator ≠ separate object
❌ 3. Confuse with Strategy
Strategy = replace behavior
Decorator = add behavior
🧠 12️⃣ Interview Killer Lines
Decorator pattern is used to add responsibilities to objects dynamically without modifying existing code.
It avoids class explosion by using composition over inheritance.
🔥 13️⃣ One Line Summary
Decorator = wrapping + layering of behavior
🧠 Final Aha (MOST IMPORTANT)
Object ko modify nahi karte,
usse wrap karke powerful banate hain

PK 🚀
Ab tum Decorator Pattern ko feel + code + system level pe samajh gaye ho:

Why needed → class explosion

How works → wrapping

Where used → real systems